Stock Portfolio Tracker in Python
A simple Python-based Stock Portfolio Tracker that allows users to enter stock names and quantities, calculates the investment value for each stock, displays a portfolio summary, and optionally saves the results to a text file.
This project is designed for beginners to practice Python fundamentals such as dictionaries, loops, conditional statements, user input handling, lists, and file operations.
Features
Track investments in predefined stocks
Calculate individual stock investment values
Calculate total portfolio value
Display a detailed investment summary
Save portfolio details to a text file
Handle invalid stock symbols gracefully
Technologies Used
Python 3
Built-in file handling
Dictionaries
Lists
Loops and conditional statements
